 domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Bluegrass_Jam_Session_-_NARA_-_7718388.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f7/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Entrance_to_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718389.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Entrance_to_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718389.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f7/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Entrance_to_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718389.jpg","cap":"Entrance to Tallgrass Prairie National Preserve","desc":"Beckoning travelers into the national preserve, this entry sign hints of the scenic prairie and historic ranching experiences ahead. Location: Kansas (38.432° N 96.557° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Entrance_to_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718389.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_First_Sunday_Motorcyclists_Gathering_-_NARA_-_7718396.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_First_Sunday_Motorcyclists_Gathering_-_NARA_-_7718396.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_First_Sunday_Motorcyclists_Gathering_-_NARA_-_7718396.jpg","cap":"First Sunday Motorcyclists Gathering","desc":"From May to October on the first Sunday of the month, motorcyclists gather in Cassoday for brunch, visiting, browsing street vendors, and having a wonderful time. Location: Kansas (38.661° N 96.492° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Al Slater, Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_First_Sunday_Motorcyclists_Gathering_-_NARA_-_7718396.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Rodeo_-_NARA_-_7718392.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Rodeo_-_NARA_-_7718392.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4d/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Rodeo_-_NARA_-_7718392.jpg","cap":"Flint Hills Rodeo","desc":"Like a scene straight out of the Old West, this horse comes barreling out of the shoots with a rider clinging to it's back. Location: Kansas (38.401° N 96.533° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Travel Tourism, Jon Hardesty","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Rodeo_-_NARA_-_7718392.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Spring_Prairie_Fire_-_NARA_-_7718399.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Spring_Prairie_Fire_-_NARA_-_7718399.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/11/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Spring_Prairie_Fire_-_NARA_-_7718399.jpg","cap":"Flint Hills Spring Prairie Fire","desc":"Periodic fire is essential to the preservation of the Tallgrass Prairie. The Prairie Fire Festival celebrates the importance of the flames every year. Location: Kansas (38.437° N 96.569° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Geological Survey","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Flint_Hills_Spring_Prairie_Fire_-_NARA_-_7718399.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/31/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_K-177_Kiosk_in_Cassoday%2C_Kansas_-_NARA_-_7718398.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/31/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_K-177_Kiosk_in_Cassoday%2C_Kansas_-_NARA_-_7718398.jpg","cap":"K 177 Kiosk in Cassoday, Kansas","desc":"This kiosk describes the brief history of Cassoday and provides information on the Flint Hills Scenic Byway. Location: Cassoday, Kansas (38.039° N 96.639° W) Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_K-177_Kiosk_in_Cassoday,_Kansas_-_NARA_-_7718398.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Little_John_Creek_Valley_-_NARA_-_7718393.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Little_John_Creek_Valley_-_NARA_-_7718393.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/58/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Little_John_Creek_Valley_-_NARA_-_7718393.jpg","cap":"Little John Creek Valley","desc":"One of Kaw Heritage Park's trails meanders beside this creek where the trees hang over the water to create a serene, safe haven. Location: Kansas (38.676° N 96.502° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kaw Mission Historic Site","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Little_John_Creek_Valley_-_NARA_-_7718393.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Madonna_of_the_Plains_Sculpture_-_NARA_-_7718395.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Madonna_of_the_Plains_Sculpture_-_NARA_-_7718395.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Madonna_of_the_Plains_Sculpture_-_NARA_-_7718395.jpg","cap":"Madonna of the Plains Sculpture","desc":"A pioneer woman and her two children stand as an example of courage to all those who visit Council Grove. Location: Kansas (38.662° N 96.490° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Travel Tourism","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Madonna_of_the_Plains_Sculpture_-_NARA_-_7718395.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Neosho_Riverwalk_at_the_Santa_Fe_Trail_River_Crossing_-_NARA_-_7718401.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Neosho_Riverwalk_at_the_Santa_Fe_Trail_River_Crossing_-_NARA_-_7718401.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/9/96/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Neosho_Riverwalk_at_the_Santa_Fe_Trail_River_Crossing_-_NARA_-_7718401.jpg","cap":"Neosho Riverwalk at the Santa Fe Trail River Crossing","desc":"The trailhead sign welcomes visitors to take a walk through a vibrant stretch of scenery on a summer's day. Location: Kansas (38.659° N 96.487° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Neosho_Riverwalk_at_the_Santa_Fe_Trail_River_Crossing_-_NARA_-_7718401.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Pioneer_Bluffs%2C_Rogler_Ranch_Historic_District_-_NARA_-_7718404.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Pioneer_Bluffs%2C_Rogler_Ranch_Historic_District_-_NARA_-_7718404.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e3/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Pioneer_Bluffs%2C_Rogler_Ranch_Historic_District_-_NARA_-_7718404.jpg","cap":"Pioneer Bluffs, Rogler Ranch Historic District","desc":"Though not open to the public, the Pioneer Bluffs offer a well-preserved example of limestone fencing for those driving by along the Byway. Location: Kansas (38.144° N 96.495° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Pioneer_Bluffs,_Rogler_Ranch_Historic_District_-_NARA_-_7718404.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/08/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Prairie_Wildflowers_at_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718406.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/08/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Prairie_Wildflowers_at_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718406.jpg","cap":"Prairie Wildflowers at Tallgrass Prairie National Preserve","desc":"Flowers soak in the sunshine at Tallgrass Prairie National Preserve along Flint Hills Scenic Byway. Location: Tallgrass Prairie National Preserve, Kansas (38.437° N 96.576° W) Status: Public domain.","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Prairie_Wildflowers_at_Tallgrass_Prairie_National_Preserve_-_NARA_-_7718406.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0e/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Strong_City_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718394.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/0e/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Strong_City_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718394.jpg","cap":"Strong City Kiosk","desc":"The Strong City kiosk tells the story of the railroad's importance for the city, the Flint Hills Rodeo, and the Tallgrass Prairie National Preserve, as well as other important information. Location: Kansas (38.400° N 96.539° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Strong_City_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718394.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Kaw_Indian_Mission_in_Council_Grove_-_NARA_-_7718390.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Kaw_Indian_Mission_in_Council_Grove_-_NARA_-_7718390.jpg","cap":"The Kaw Indian Mission in Council Grove","desc":"A clear blue sky contrasts nicely with the white limestone architecture of this mission. Location: Kansas (38.661° N 96.491° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of Kansas Scenic Byways Program","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Kaw_Indian_Mission_in_Council_Grove_-_NARA_-_7718390.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Vast_Tallgrass_Prairie_in_the_Flint_Hills_-_NARA_-_7718391.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Vast_Tallgrass_Prairie_in_the_Flint_Hills_-_NARA_-_7718391.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/82/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Vast_Tallgrass_Prairie_in_the_Flint_Hills_-_NARA_-_7718391.jpg","cap":"The Vast Tallgrass Prairie in the Flint Hills","desc":"The vastness of the Tallgrass Prairie can only be seen to fully appreciate its grandeur. As the last large contiguous remnant of tallgrass prairie on earth, the Flint Hills Tallgrass Prairie offers an unspoiled landscape of serene natural beauty. Location: Kansas (38.437° N 96.571° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Mike Blair, Kansas Department of Wildlife and Parks","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_The_Vast_Tallgrass_Prairie_in_the_Flint_Hills_-_NARA_-_7718391.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b6/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Wagon_Train_Excursion_-_NARA_-_7718405.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Wagon_Train_Excursion_-_NARA_-_7718405.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b6/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Wagon_Train_Excursion_-_NARA_-_7718405.jpg","cap":"Wagon Train Excursion","desc":"A cowboy overlooks camp as the sun sets on another day's hard work. Location: Kansas (38.400° N 96.531° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Travel and Tourism, Jon Hardesty","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Wagon_Train_Excursion_-_NARA_-_7718405.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Z-Bar_or_Spring_Hill_Ranch_House_-_NARA_-_7718400.jpg/1280px-Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Z-Bar_or_Spring_Hill_Ranch_House_-_NARA_-_7718400.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c9/Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Z-Bar_or_Spring_Hill_Ranch_House_-_NARA_-_7718400.jpg","cap":"Z Bar or Spring Hill Ranch House","desc":"Built in the 1880s, this eleven-room limestone ranch home stands gracefully on the hillside. Location: Kansas (38.400° N 96.539° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Kansas Travel Tourism","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flint_Hills_Scenic_Byway_-_Z-Bar_or_Spring_Hill_Ranch_House_-_NARA_-_7718400.jpg"}]}